    title: "DSSSB JSA Typing Test 18",
    difficulty: "Medium",
    text: `It has been the kind of year when the news in India feels closer to the kitchen table than to a distant studio, and every big headline seems to arrive with a small question about what it means for bills, bus rides, and the next school fee, so the tone of twenty twenty five has become quietly practical and a little hopeful too. Budget talk did not stop at numbers this time, it ran into neighborhoods where roadwork finally shortens a commute, where a new station lift helps an elder travel with dignity, and where a mason sees steady shifts because bridges and warehousing are more than plans on a slide. Farmers measured promises against skies and markets, reading about better seeds storage and transport with the patient eye of people who know that a week of late rain can erase a season, and they still welcomed simple improvements like a working cold room, a fair truck rate, and a buyer who pays on time. In small workshops, the idea of cash flow lending made sense in the most ordinary way, because a tailor or a repair shop owner does not own heavy assets but does have orders and receipts that tell a real story, and fewer forms means less time away from the tools that feed a family. Health news felt human in the details, with more talk of district level care, day care cancer services, and diagnostics a bus ride away rather than a train journey that eats courage and money, and nurses kept reminding everyone that prevention is not a speech but a habit made of clean data, follow up, and steady supplies. Schools and skilling centers tried to make learning less fragile by adding apprenticeships and simple labs where a student can handle a tool, run a checklist, and learn to fix a problem under a kind eye, because confidence grows when theory meets a real task. On energy, the conversation turned from slogans to fittings and bills, as rooftop solar, biogas, and cleaner fuels met the honest reality of dust, heat, and monsoon weeks, while smarter metering and sturdier feeders made the monthly bill less of a surprise for homes and shops that plan day by day. Digital public rails kept doing quiet work in the background,`
